<br>
The reason I petitioned is I am nearly a GM tailor, and a halfling tailor at that.  Even the 'free' bags was a nail in my heart, knowing how much work I have put into this all too time consuming tradeskill.<br>
<br>
You see, as a halfling, one of our cultural tailoring items are <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Leatherfoot Bags</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, with the 10 slot 100% WR GIANT size versions at a 250+ trivial.  Basically I watched any market for these bags go down the toilet yesterday.  And hard to make?  It takes 3 BD's/3 plat threads and a 9 foraged dire wolf furs to even <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> attempt</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> a Leatherfoot Bag.<br>
<br>
So this NO DROP bug yesterday had more far reaching implications...kudos to those that got one, and thus exploited Verants folly.  And my heart goes out to those halflings who had any aspirations at selling Leatherfoot Bags.   <p><center>


