<br>
I've never understood the economics behind the Halfling tailored bag anyway.  Even if you have three Blue Diamonds in your possession already, and don't need to buy them, you could easily dump them on the market at 2k per.  That's less than almost anyone is asking these days.  The 10 slot 100% bag that is *purchased* down in Sol A costs 5250. I think it's great that the tailoring skill is there, because I approve of players being able to make things, but I don't imagine it is any sort of gold mine.<br>
