<br>
As a monk, I currently have two 0.4 wt 100% (there are only two in game) and this 1.2 wt 100% GM carry-all.  I want 3 more tinkerer's and I will be replacing the GM bag with a tinkerer because saving 0.2 is a nice upgrade.  When I can, I will be replacing all tinkerer's with LF bags for another 1.2 total savings.<br>
<br>
So, all your fears about LF bags not being wanted are completely unfounded.  The GM bags do absolutely nothing to the LF bag market and they would continue to do nothing to LF bag market even if they were handed out for free just by hailing Jolum. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujaranna.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jaranna</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/24/02 6:31:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1262.topic&index=46>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_tongue.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: LOL Twig</span><hr size=1> As a wizard of Solusek Ro, I have access to imbued fire opal jewelry.  These rings have a negative strength bonus smilar to their INT bonus.<br>
<br>
I wear two imbued platinum fire rings.  That's -8 STR each for -16 STR total.  As a wizard, my strength isn't all that great in the first place.  So, yes.  ANY bags with weight reduction are wanted.  It's very hard to loot something when you're going to be encumbered just from carrying it.<br>
<br>
I currently have 3 weight reduction bags (in addition to the backpacks I've made): Evil eye, rallic pack and the grandmaster's carry-all.  I prize them all.  I'm damn jealous at the halflings, too, because I want to GM in tailoring myself, but because I'm human, I don't get to make those bags.<br>
<br>
Long post, but the point is, there is still a market for those haversacks and such.  Maybe not from the warriors and their ilk, but those of us who can't lift a fine steel weapon without severe arm strain love them. <p><P>Jaranna<BR>
